The defendant Edward Tyrone Riser was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Trespass to Dwelling [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Penalty-Theft if Value <=$2500, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Petitioner DID NOT appear  . State of Wisconsin appear by Assistant District Attorney DENIS STINGL
Deputy Court Clerk: LR
  Court denies petition FOR RETURN OF PROPERTY.

Defendant Edward Tyrone Riser in court with attorney Daryl A. Kastenson.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2:    Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state, defense counsel and defendant. 

Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, straight time, concurrent to each other, with credit for 4 days time served. 

COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 years under the supervision of Wisconsin Department of Corrections.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 
* Comply with the standard rules of extended supervision.
* SERVE 90 DAYS "condition time" - STAYED provided that the defendant continues to work.  If defendant is not employed, he is to serve the condition time with release privileges for school and employment searches.
* No contact with the victim, Beatrice S.
* Cooperate and participate with an AODA assessment and follow any recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety and submit to random urine screens.
* PAY restitution in the amount of $500.00 payable to the victim, Beatrice S. - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY the DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

Appeal rights given.

Defendant Edward Tyrone Riser in court with attorney Daryl A. Kastenson.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Upon State's motion and pursuant to negotiations, Court AMENDS Count 1 to two misdemeanor charges as follows:

Count 1:  Criminal Trespass to Dwelling [a Class A MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 943.14, 939.51(3)(a).
Count 2:  Theft (Value Not Exceeding $2,500) [a Class A MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 943.20(1)(a) and (3)(a), 939.51(3)(a).

AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2 (AMENDED):  Defendant pled GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
